cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.PL 

The paper addresses the problem of discovering communication links between applications in the Android mobile operating system, which is a security and privacy concern. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the category of Computer Security and Cryptography (cs.CR). The paper proposes to use a trained neural-network model to improve the precision of static analysis, which suggests that it may also belong to the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also describes a neural-network architecture that encodes abstractions of communicating objects, which suggests that it may belong to the category of Programming Languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on a large corpus of Android applications, which suggests that it may also belong to the category of Software Engineering (cs.SE).
